message.content:
To determine how long one notepad will last, we need to calculate the total number of notes that can be made from one notepad.
First, let's figure out how many smaller note papers can be made from one letter size piece of paper. When Harmony folds a letter size piece of paper three times, it creates 8 smaller note papers (2^3 = 8).
Next, we need to calculate how many letter size pieces of paper are needed to make one notepad. Since Harmony stacks the smaller note papers together and staples them, she will use one piece of paper for each notepad.
Now we can calculate how many notes can be made from one notepad:
8 smaller note papers x 1 notepad = 8 notes
If someone writes 10 notes per day, then one notepad would last:
8 notes / 10 notes/day = 0. 8 days or 20 hours
